<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIVILIANS CAPTURE LEADER OF FAILED COUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Civilians Friday captured, beat and stripped the leader of a failed coup 
disguised as an Arab and handed him over to African intervention troops. 
</P>
<P>
 Former armed forces chief Charles Julue led about 100 disgruntled soldiers who 
briefly seized the West African country's seat of power Thursday. They were 
forced out by a massive assault by an African intervention force. 
</P>
<P>
 Battles between two other militias in the southeast sent refugees across the 
Cavally River into Ivory Coast, where 2,000 arrived in Tabou in 24 hours and 
thousands more awaited canoes to bring them over, a relief worker said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
