<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO OFFICERS LIABLE IN PAPER SEIZURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Police Chief Richard Hongisto committed civil rights violations in the 
removal of a newspaper from its racks, a jury found Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel decided Hongisto and two officers committed the violations by 
removing from news racks 2,000 copies of a free newspaper that lampooned the 
chief for ordering mass arrests of demonstrators after the verdict in the first 
Rodney G. King trial. A cartoon showed the chief in a lewd pose. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. District Court jury awarded $5,600 to the Bay Times for losses and 
$30,000 to its editor for emotional distress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
