<HEADLINE>
<P>
WYNN FILES LIBEL SUIT AGAINST LAS VEGAS PAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Casino mogul Steve Wynn has filed a lawsuit against a Las Vegas tabloid, 
charging that the weekly publication libeled him in May by suggesting that he 
participated in money laundering and his daughter's kidnaping. 
</P>
<P>
 Wynn, chairman of Mirage Resorts Inc., filed the suit in District Court 
against Casino News, writer Debra Percell and the Center for Academic Research 
& Endowment. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the document, Casino News ran an article May 18 in which Percell 
asked: "Who was really trying to launder money? Wynn or Cuddy? Would Steve 
stoop so low as to involve his own daughter in such a scheme?" 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have never named Wynn as a suspect in the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
