</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Being an avid Rams fan since childhood, Larry Stewart's article made me livid. 
</P>
<P>
 Why on earth would I rather watch Joe Montana play the 49ers instead of my 
hometown team, the L.A. Rams? It was yet another reminder that this is a town 
that loves to put down the Rams. 
</P>
<P>
 I'm a Los Angeles native and I root for the L.A. teams no matter how good they 
are from year to year. 
</P>
<P>
 MARTIN WALSH 
</P>
<P>
 Tujunga 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Because the Rams are a Southern California team, we were force fed only one 
game -- the Rams at Atlanta -- rather than seeing the 49ers-Chiefs game. 
</P>
<P>
 Georgia, please move your team out of Southern California so that we football 
fans can watch good football. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES MENCONI 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
