<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cornerback Todd Lyght is beginning his fourth season with the Rams and still 
looking for his first victory over the 49ers. 
</P>
<P>
 To achieve success, Lyght said, it begins with him and his play on 49er wide 
receiver Jerry Rice. 
</P>
<P>
 Rice, the NFL's all-time leader in touchdowns with 127, has scored 11 against 
the Rams and has more yards receiving against the Rams, 1,527, than against any 
other team.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's comparable to going out and trying to D-up Michael Jordan," Lyght said. 
"He's going to get some, but you have to make it so he's not going to be the 
game-breaker." T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
