<P>
CLASSICAL MUSIC MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thanks to Lynne Heffley, Los Angeles is now aware that September is Classical 
Music Month, and she gave suggestions for good listening ("Classical Music Hits 
the Right Notes for Children," Sept. 6). 
</P>
<P>
 But classical music needs everyone's participation! Adults and children alike 
should celebrate by getting involved in some classical music.Join a choir, take 
up a new or neglected musical instrument, perform chamber music, provide 
lessons for someone, play a recording for a friend, listen to classical music 
radio, take a friend to the Philharmonic. 
</P>
<P>
 Rep. Sidney R. Yates (D-Ill.) got the proclamation through Congress. Let's 
write to our representatives and request that our state reinstitute music 
programs in every school. Let's demand support for federal arts funding on the 
level of every other civilized nation. 
</P>
<P>
