<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; COUNCIL 
ACTION POSTPONED ON JOBS TRAINING GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Council action was postponed Friday on a $3-million federal grant for a 
youth job training and placement center in South-Central Los Angeles when the 
council meeting was canceled because of a quorum. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the members who were absent were Mark Ridley-Thomas and Rita Walters, 
both of whom had previously raised questions about a federal decision to award 
a contract, without seeking bids, to the Community Build riot recovery 
organization. 
</P>
<P>
 The private Leimert Park-based agency, which has a limited track record in 
undertaking job training projects, plans to serve youngsters in neighborhoods 
in Ridley-Thomas' and Walters' council districts. 
</P>
<P>
 The two council members had no comment on their absence. Councilman Mike 
Hernandez, a proponent of the program, said the pair had indicated they did not 
want to vote in favor of the project but did not want to see it killed, either. 
</P>
</TEXT>
