<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; MISSION TO RING WITH GREGORIAN 
CHANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Schola Pacifica, a men's chorus specializing in Gregorian chants, will perform 
in concert tonight at Mission San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 The San Diego-based group is part of the mission's summer series of concerts 
under the stars.The show starts at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The group, which is not tied to any church sponsorship, includes members who 
are Catholic, Protestant and Jewish. The group has recorded a compact disc that 
is selling in national music stores. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the concert are $5 for adults, $3 for seniors and children 12 and 
under. Dinners are available for sale at the mission or concert goers may bring 
their own meals. 
</P>
<P>
 Limited seating is provided. People are encouraged to bring folding chairs. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 248-2049.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
