<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; OPPOSITION AGAINST MALL PLAN GROWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Opposition is heating up against a proposed major expansion of the Sherman 
Oaks Fashion Square mall. 
</P>
<P>
 A group of 700 residents who live near the shopping mall has distributed 700 
flyers decrying the project. 
</P>
<P>
 Tybe Drum, president of the Sherman Oaks Property Owners Assn., said that in 
the next week her group will be sending out another 300 flyers, which urge 
residents to oppose the project at a public hearing scheduled for Sept. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Drum said her group fears the project would create problems of roadway 
congestion, traffic safety and air pollution. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our neighborhoods will be ruined over it," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fashion Square is proposing a $20-million expansion that would increase the 
size of the mall by nearly 20%, to 975,000 square feet. The project would allow 
Fashion Square to increase the amount of space available for a third anchor 
store to 180,000 square feet. Mall representatives say that much space would 
enable them to attract an upscale department store, such as Nordstrom or 
Bloomingdale's. 
</P>
<P>
 Mall officials say the community wants another department store to replace I. 
Magnin, which left late last year. They said 1,000 people have signed a 
petition in support of the store. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
