<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; CITY OFFERING TRASH COMPOST BINS FOR $15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To reduce the amount of trash going from Moorpark to landfills, the city is 
encouraging residents to let their organic waste rot in easy-to-maintain 
compost bins. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has about 100 bins it is offering them to residents for $15.The bins 
often cost $99 in stores, according to Jill Rubin Myers, Moorpark's solid waste 
coordinator. 
</P>
<P>
 Composting yard clippings and food scraps can reduce the trash produced in a 
year from one household by nearly a third of a ton, Myers said. 
</P>
<P>
 The composting bins allow trash to biodegrade with little or no odor into a 
fertile soil amendment that can be used in the garden or for house plants, 
Myers said.  
</P>
<P>
 The bins will be on sale Oct. 1 at Moorpark Country Days. A free book on 
composting is included in the offer. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Myers at 529-6864, Ext. 248. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
