<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE IDENTIFY BODY OF SLAIN MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have identified a bullet-riddled body found Aug. 8 near a construction 
site as that of a 19-year-old Santa Ana man. 
</P>
<P>
 Gustavo Hernandez's burned and partially decomposed body was found in the area 
of Diamante and Calle Fino Clarete by two people searching for a lost animal.He 
had been shot several times in the chest, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez's 19-year-old girlfriend, whose identity was not released by police, 
last saw him Aug. 4 and reported him missing to Santa Ana police on Sept. 5, 
according to Orange County Sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini. 
</P>
<P>
 After newspapers published a police composite drawing of the victim the 
girlfriend contacted the Sheriff's Department to say it resembled Hernandez. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez was then identified through a thumbprint from his California 
identification papers supplied by his family, police said. 
</P>
