<TEXT>
<P>
 Stock car driver Ernie Irvan, who survived life-threatening head and lung 
injuries in a crash at a Michigan track last month, returned to Charlotte on 
Friday to continue his rehabilitation. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvan was moved to the Charlotte Institute of Rehabilitation from St. Joseph 
Mercy Hospital in Ann Arbor, Mich., where he had been since his accident at 
Michigan International Speedway on Aug. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 At a news conference in Charlotte, Dr. James T. McDeavitt said Irvan will 
undergo tests before starting on a rehabilitation schedule lasting six to eight 
hours a day. 
