<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NO. 1 CORONA DEL MAR LOSES IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Robby Arroyo scored the game-winning goal in overtime to give 
fourth-ranked Foothill a 9-8 victory over No. 1-ranked Corona del Mar in a 
nonleague water polo match Friday at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Arroyo, whose brother Gavin plays with the U.S. National Water Polo team, 
scored the winning goal off a drive and a pick 32 seconds into overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill took an early three-goal lead in the first quarter but the Sea Kings, 
led by James Palda with four goals, answered with five consecutive goals. 
Corona del Mar led 7-4 midway through the fourth quarter but the Knights came 
back with the four goals, with Brian Brown scoring the game-tying goal with 
1:10 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Brown had nine saves for Foothill, which improves to 1-1. Corona del Mar 
is 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 23, La Quinta 3 -- Bret Trezise scored eight goals and John Roy 
added four for host Saddleback (4-1). The Roadrunners led, 9-0, after one 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 27, Orange 1 -- Scott Baker scored 11 goals and Justin Link had five 
goals and eight assists in the Troy (6-0) victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In a quarterfinal of the Long Beach Millikan Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 13, Ventura Buena 5 -- Juniors Peter Cornue and Brian Pharris paced 
the Villa Park's offense, combining for eight goals. Cornue had five goals and 
Pharris added three. Goalie Brett Galaway had six saves for Villa Park (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the third round: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara San Marcos 6, Edison 3 -- Darren Wynns scored two goals and Kirk 
McMahan recorded 10 saves in a losing effort as San Marcos (2-1) defeated 
Edison (3-2) in third-round play. Edison took a 3-1 lead, but failed to hold 
the lead and were shutout in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 In pool play of the Riverside Poly water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 8, South Pasadena 7 -- Steve Popov and Sean Hylton each scored 
three goals to lead Costa Mesa (4-0) over South Pasadena (3-1). Popov scored 
the game-winning goal with 34 seconds left in the match. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 18, San Diego Monte Vista 3 -- Stever O'Rourke had six goals, Lance 
Banuk had five and Eric Larson added four as Marina won a pool-play game to 
remain undefeated at 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 11, Costa Mesa 7 -- Liza Scheller and Duyen Pham swept at No. 2 doubles 
for Orange (4-0) and Jeannette Maher swept at No. 3 singles for the host 
Mustangs (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 10, University 8 -- Yuka Suzuki and Brooke Stevens won their No. 1 
double matches, 6-1, 6-3, 7-5 for Woodbridge (3-1). 
</P>
