<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; NEWPORT HARBOR, KAGASOFF 
DOMINATE OCEAN VIEW, 28-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paced by two touchdowns from Edon Kagasoff and a strong defensive effort, 
Newport Harbor dominated visiting Ocean View, 28-0, in a nonleague game in 
front of 1,200 Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Kagasoff, who scored on runs of seven and 44 yards, led all rushers with 57 
yards in six carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensively, Bill Johns and Dan McDonough frustrated the Seahawks, extending 
the Golden West League team's losing streak to 31 games, currently the state's 
longest. 
</P>
<P>
 Johns finished the night with two sacks for Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 "We got a little sloppy at times," Sailor Coach Jeff Brinkley said. "We 
definitely weren't as crisp as last week." 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors (2-0) took command early, driving 65 yards in 10 plays on its 
first possession, eventually scoring on a one-yard run by Brian Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View (0-2), which was held to only three total yards offense in the 
first half, opened the second half with its only substantial drive. The 
Seahawks used 16 plays to advance to the Sailor 32-yard line before Johnson 
intercepted a Ted Norman pass in the end zone to end the threat. MATT FARMER 
</P>
