<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOSEPH WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wilson 20, Monroe 19 -- Wilson stopped Quincy Brooks on a two-point conversion 
attempt in the final minute of the game to thwart the Vikings at Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing 20-13 in the fourth quarter, Monroe launched a 67-yard drive in 10 
plays, capped by a 20-yard scoring pass from Brooks to tight end Tryone 
Frost.Brooks was stuffed by Wilson at the one-yard line on the two-point 
attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe (0-2) failed to move the ball in the first half and trailed, 14-0. 
However, two interceptions in the second half set up scoring runs by Brooks, 
who started the game as a running back but finished as quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Gonzalez of Wilson (2-0) threw three touchdown passes but also threw 
three interceptions. JOSEPH WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
