<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLY BULL FAVORED IN THE WOODWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Today's Woodward Stakes at Belmont Park will feature a showdown between 
Kentucky Derby winner Go For Gin and Holy Bull, a leading horse-of-the-year 
candidate who beat Preakness and Belmont winner Tabasco Cat in the Travers his 
last time out. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the race of the year so far," said Scotty Schulhofer, who will saddle 
1993 Belmont Stakes winner Colonial Affair for the race. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on today's Belmont card will be two Grade I, $100,000-added stakes for 
juveniles, the Futurity and Matron; the Vosburgh, a seven-furlong sprint worth 
$200,000; the $400,000 Man o' War on grass, and the $200,000 Ruffian, featuring 
two of the country's top females in Sky Beauty and Dispute. 
</P>
<P>
 The purses total more than $1.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The Woodward field from the rail out, with jockeys and morning-line odds: 
Tinners Way, Pat Day, 5-1; Devil His Due, Jerry Bailey, 4-1; Go For Gin, Chris 
McCarron, 9-2; Pistols And Roses, Jorge Velasquez, 20-1; Holy Bull, Mike Smith, 
8-5; Brunswick, Julie Krone, 10-1; Bertrando, Pat Valenzuela, 6-1, and Colonial 
Affair, Jose Santos, 8-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The older horses will carry 126 pounds under weight-for-age conditions, while 
the two 3-year-olds, Go For Gin and Holy Bull, are assigned 121. The winner 
will earn $300,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
