<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRESPI SPUTTERS AGAINST CANYON SPRINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETE MARSHALL, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There were no come-from-behind heroics for Crespi High this week. 
</P>
<P>
 It started badly -- and stayed that way for 48 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi managed just three first downs in the first half and never got on 
track, suffering a 38-15 setback to Canyon Springs in a nonleague game Friday 
at Valley View High. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon Springs (1-1), ranked No. 20 in the state by Cal-Hi Sports, amassed 248 
yards in the first half to fuel a 20-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Crespi (1-1), which overcame a 13-point deficit in the second half 
to beat Taft, 20-19, last week, sputtered throughout. 
</P>
<P>
 Terrelle Smith rushed for 87 yards and two touchdowns for Canyon Springs. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 20-0, late in the first half, Crespi appeared to turn its fortunes 
around when Mark Stipkovich recovered a fumble and returned it 80 yards for a 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 But Crespi couldn't mount an offense after intermission. Only a 21-yard 
touchdown pass from Dave Lins to Wayne Emerson in the final minute kept the 
Crespi offense from being shut out. 
</P>
<P>
 One week after throwing for more than 200 yards, Lins completed only nine of 
18 passes for 108 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
