<HEADLINE>
<P>
ST. GENEVIEVE HALTED BY PARACLETE DEFENSE; FOOTBALL: VALIANT EFFORT RESULTS IN 
NEGATIVE YARDAGE. PARACLETE RECORDS EIGHT SACKS, TWO INTERCEPTIONS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Dagata scored touchdowns on a pass and an interception return to lead 
Paraclete High to an impressive 24-0 victory over St. Genevieve Friday night at 
Antelope Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Dagata opened the scoring with a 45-yard interception return. 
</P>
<P>
 His second touchdown came on a five-yard pass from quarterback Robbie Wood. 
</P>
<P>
 Wood completed 13 of 23 passes for 111 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 His other touchdown pass was a seven-yard strike to Ian Savage in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Paraclete (1-1) dominated on defense as well, registering eight sacks and two 
interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spirits limited the Valiants (0-2) to minus-three yards. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Genevieve couldn't move and quarterback Randy Iaccino did not last the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 He injured his ankle early in the second half and did not return to the 
lineup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
