<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUGUS IS DOMINANT IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULE WOODS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeremy Mushinski had 86 yards in 14 carries and scored the first four 
touchdowns to lead Saugus to a 41-0 victory over Palmdale Friday night at 
Palmdale High. 
</P>
<P>
 Mushinski, a senior tailback, scored on runs of two, one, two and one yards to 
give Saugus (2-0) a 26-0 lead midway through the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Linebacker Matt Gillis had six sacks and led a stellar performance by the 
Centurian defense, which forced five fumbles and recovered four. 
</P>
<P>
 " 'Oh no, not No. 89 again,' that quarterback must have been saying," Saugus 
Coach Jack Bowman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus quarterback Kevin Carrasco completed four of 10 passes for 101 yards. 
He had two passes intercepted. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale's Gerald Brown intercepted a pass by Carrasco at the Saugus 30-yard 
line and returned it 22 yards, but the first Falcon fumble ended the scoring 
threat. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale quarterback Phillip Paez completed two of six passes for 12 yards in 
the first quarter, but was replaced by Johnny Gillespie in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Gillespie completed five of 11 passes for 34 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The lone offensive bright spot for the Falcons (0-2) came on a 25-yard run by 
Janel White in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "Palmdale is a young team and Coach (Jeff) Williams plays tough teams in the 
preseason," Bowman said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our kids on defense wanted to do something special." 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Olivares was Palmdale's leading rusher with 30 yards in nine carries. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons had nine penalties for 75 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus had nine penalties for 80 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first half, Saugus held Palmdale to only 15 yards. Saugus gained 130 
yards in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus' Colin Butterfield caught two passes for 64 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
