<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAXWELL PACES ST. FRANCIS, 28-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAUREN PETERSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Darren Maxwell rushed for 191 yards in 33 carries and scored two 
touchdowns to lead St. Francis High to a 28-7 victory over Verdugo Hills in a 
nonleague football game Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxwell caught an 11-yard scoring pass from Brian Rucker in the first quarter 
and ran two yards for another touchdown in the third quarter.Maxwell had two 
receptions for 22 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Rucker, who led St. Francis on scoring drives of 66 and 79 yards, left the 
game because of a lower back injury after connecting with tight end Chris Ross 
on a two-point conversion following the Golden Knights' second score. 
</P>
<P>
 Rucker completed four of seven passes for 78 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 In Rucker's place, reserve quarterback John Carnevali guided St. Francis 
(1-0-1) on two fourth-quarter scoring drives. 
</P>
<P>
 Carnevali threw touchdown passes of seven yards to Andrew Warnock (two 
receptions, 33 yards) and nine yards to Vince Dioguardi. 
</P>
<P>
 For Verdugo Hills, tailback Jason Evans rushed for 111 yards in 10 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback David Kelly completed two of five passes for 15 yards and provided 
the Dons' only touchdown on a 17-yard keeper, set up by a 52-yard run by Evans 
on the previous play. LAUREN PETERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
