<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; FAUSTO RUNS FREE, SCORING FIVE 
TIMES FOR LOS AMIGOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Amigos running back Greg Fausto put on a ballcarriers' clinic Friday 
night, rushing for five touchdowns and 275 yards to lead the Lobos to a 38-21 
victory at Garden Grove High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tustin defenders looked bewildered as Fausto scored four times in the 
first half on runs of 29, 10, 7 and 86 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the game Los Amigos Coach Roger Takahashi said he wasn't going to 
change anything after his team's season-opening 20-7 victory over Century last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just want to score more points this week," Takahashi said. 
</P>
<P>
 And the Lobos did. Thanks to Fausto and a defense that recorded 10 sacks. 
Jacob Sanchez had four sacks and Jose Medina had three. 
</P>
<P>
 The seventh-ranked Lobos got a fumble recovery by Sanchez on the second play 
of the game and two plays later, Fausto carried the ball in. Barely a minute 
had ticked off the clock. 
</P>
<P>
 Four downs later, the Tillers punted the ball. Fausto soon again crossing the 
goal line, this time from 10 yards out, and it was 13-0 with 6 minutes 50 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Fausto scored once more before Tustin was finally able to put points on the 
board. Senior Reggie Curry took a short pass 30 yards to cut the Lobos' lead to 
19-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Fausto came back one more time, on second and 21, when he ran through the 
Tillers' line and sprinted 86 yards for his fourth touchdown and 25-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos' other first-half score came when La Rue Carr caught a 65-yard pass 
from Ape Tuato with 36 seconds remaining and Los Amigos led, 31-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Fausto scored one more time on a 70-yard run to close out the third quarter 
and take a 38-7 lead. He would have scored a record-tying six times on the 
night, but a holding penalty nullified a three-yard touchdown run in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tillers' Brandon Lambert finished with two touchdowns, scoring in the last 
two minutes on runs of 11 and 17 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
