<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newbury Park 42, San Marcos 6 -- Senior receiver Eric Mahanke scored three 
touchdowns and the Panthers extended their winning streak to 16 games. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park exploded for 28 first-half points as quarterback Justin Vint 
connected on 11 of 15 passes for 151 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Vint finished with 186 yards, completing 12 of 22 for three touchdowns with 
one interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Brock Diediker scored the Panthers' first two touchdowns on one-yard runs 
capping drives of 71 and 35 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahanke caught eight passes for 127 yards, including scores of 26 and 35 
yards. He also returned an interception 58 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior kicker Christine Sanford set a Newbury Park school record by converting 
all six of her point-after attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Tony Robertson of Newbury Park (2-0) led all rushers with 68 
yards in 15 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park had 377 total yards and held San Marcos to 148 yards. GREG MEADE 
