</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Matt Rutter passed for two touchdowns and ran for a third to lead 
Reseda High to a 28-7 nonleague victory over neighborhood rival Cleveland 
Friday night at Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
 Rutter completed eight of nine passes for 85 yards, including touchdown passes 
of eight and 13 yards to senior Alonso Arreola.Arreola caught three passes for 
31 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Michael Oxx rushed for 73 yards in 15 carries and scored on a 
seven-yard run in the second quarter, giving the Regents (1-1) a 13-7 lead at 
halftime.  
</P>
<P>
 Oxx also intercepted a pass by Johnny Lopez to stop the Cavaliers' first 
drive. Lopez completed nine of 13 passes for 125 yards. 
</P>
