<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; ROBINSON LEADS CANYON PAST BUENA 
PARK, 27-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon overwhelmed Buena Park, 27-0, Friday night at El Modena High School, as 
the Comanches got off to a fast start for the second consecutive season. 
</P>
<P>
 Devvon Robinson scored two touchdowns for the Comanches (2-0), who were 4-0-1 
in nonleague play last season.Canyon was third in the Century League and 
qualified for the Southern Section Division IV playoffs, its first postseason 
appearance since 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson scored on an eight-yard run in the first quarter to give the 
Comanches the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Hoover, on a quarterback sneak, ran 20 yards for a touchdown in the 
second quarter. Hoover also threw a 15-yard touchdown pass to Greg Jacobs, 
giving the Comanches a 21-0 lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon also had two touchdowns called back because of penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson scored on a four-yard run in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park is 0-1-1. 
</P>
