<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; COSTA MESA ROLLS PAST 
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa piled up 495 yards on the ground and controlled the ball for more 
than 31 minutes, scoring on four of their first five possessions in beating 
Westminster, 38-14 Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Chatman led the Mustang attack with 226 yards on 19 carries and three 
touchdowns.Dewayne Crenshaw added 117 yards, all in the first half for the 
Mustangs (2-0). Crenshaw, who is recovering from a fractured wrist, piled up 
248 yards in last week's 50-6 victory over Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatman scored on runs of 7, 49, and 22 yards on the first three Mustang 
possessions of the game to build a 22-0 lead. Westminster nearly got back a 
touchdown before the intermission, but Todd Mann dropped a Jerry Allison pass 
at the goal line and the Lions eventually turned the ball over on downs. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa added another score early in the third quarter, as Chatman runs of 
24 and 30 led to Brian Reeves' 7-yard scoring dash. 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster did not go quietly. Leonard Ibarra returned the ensuing kickoff 73 
yards to get the Lions on the board, and a 74-yard Allison-to-David Kurien pass 
set up an 18-yard touchdown run from Allison. 
</P>
<P>
 After the teams exchanged fumbles, Costa Mesa added another touchdown, this 
one on a 27-yard pass from Ryan Taylor to Josh Amezola, to take a 38-14 lead 
and put the contest out of reach. ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
