ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; RANCHO ALAMITOS' YOUNG GAINS 254 
YARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CATHY LALKO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sparked by a 254-yard performance by senior Chris Young, Rancho Alamitos 
defeated Aliso Niguel, 36-12, at Bolsa Grande Stadium in Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Allen scored three times on runs of three, two, and 12 yards out and 
caught a 27-yard touchdown toss from John Frank. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos grabbed a 6-0 lead 1 minute 48 seconds into the second quarter 
on a three-yard run by Allen. The scoring drive took 2:50 and was aided by 
five-yard face mask and illegal participation penalties against Aliso Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel answered on a Scott Nemeth-to-Deangelo Gossett 44-yard completion 
with 1:26 left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 With one second left in the half, Rancho Alamitos took a 15-6 lead on a 
27-yard pass from Frank to Allen and the two-point conversion pass from Aaron 
Trigg to Jeff Turbarg. Allen also caught a pass for 39 yards on the drive. The 
drive took eight seconds and two plays and began with Tom Navarro's 
interception of Nemeth. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos' offense dominated the second half scoring three touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The only other Aliso Niguel score came on a six-yard Nemeth throw to Joe 
Valenti. CATHY LALKO 
</P>
