</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Daven King rushed for 157 yards and three touchdowns and quarterback Jeremy 
Klemp had a near-flawless performance to lead Savanna to a 42-6 victory over 
Katella Friday at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna used a variety of run-and-shoot plays that kept the Knights guessing 
throughout.When King wasn't exhausting Katella's defense with his elusive 
speed, Klemp was completing all but one of his passes. He finished with 12 
completions in 13 attempts for 157 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rebels scored on their first possession when King, who rushed only 10 
times in the game, raced up the middle for a 23-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Early in the second quarter, leading 7-0, Savanna drove to the Katella 
five-yard line on a 29-yard run by King. Four consecutive running plays failed 
to reach the end zone. Katella took over but was forced to punt from its three. 
King returned the punt 28 yards and set up a sneak by Klemp. 
</P>
<P>
 After Savanna defensive back Dedrick Ennis intercepted a pass late in the 
half, the Rebels scored when Klemp hit Berry Micheel on a nine-yard scoring 
pass. COREY LYONS 
