<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodland Hills West routed an eight-team field to win the 1989 American Legion 
World Series in Millington, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills, composed of players from El Camino Real and Canoga Park highs, 
became the first team from the region to win the Series title, a feat that was 
duplicated in 1992 by Newbury Oaks. The latter was composed of players from 
Thousand Oaks and Newbury Park highs. 
</P>
