<P>
 Laguna Beach won its first game of the season, beating determined El Segundo, 
7-0, in front more than 850 Friday night at Laguna Beach High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Artists scored on a three-play drive in the waning moments of the first 
half.Quarterback Nate Tivaroff completed a 16-yard pass to wide receiver Zeda 
Stone, who streaked into the end zone. 
