<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; SONORA USES GROUND ATTACK TO RUN 
DOWN SANTIAGO, 35-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TED APODOCA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sonora High went to its ground game to grind out a 35-6 victory over Santiago 
Friday night at La Habra High School. Three Sonora running backs combined to 
gain 196 yards, including 96 from Shawn Brass. 
</P>
<P>
 Brass, who sat out last week with an ankle injury, scored on a 51-yard run in 
the third quarter that gave the Raiders (1-1) a 28-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Kevin Rodriguez passed for 140 yards as Sonora took as 13-0 lead 
in the first quarter. Rodriguez threw a two-yard touchdown pass to Albert Lopez 
in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora got a break in the first quarter when a 60-yard pass play was nullified 
by a penalty. The Cavaliers (0-2) did not realize that the illegal forward pass 
infraction included a loss of down and turned the ball over after a fourth-down 
running play. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Escobar scored two plays later on 15-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 On the Raiders' next possession, Rodriguez completed a 30-yard pass to 
Escobar. Two plays later, Rodriguez scored on a one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cavaliers only score came after a blocked punt by Tom Sokantrong, which 
gave Santiago the ball on the two. Christian Cortez scored on two-yard run on 
the next play. TED APODOCA 
