<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL PREP EXTRA; CHAMBERS LEADS WESTERN PAST 
CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dean Chambers passed for 196 yards and two touchdowns to lead host Western 
past Cypress, 29-16, at Western High. 
</P>
<P>
 Chambers completed 11 of 19 passes, including seven of his first nine 
attempts.He connected on a 21-yard touchdown pass to Andy Lee with 7:14 in the 
second quarter to give the Pioneers (2-0) a 7-3 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (1-1) answered back with an 80-yard touchdown pass from David Wheeler 
to Bobby Brito on the Centurions' first play. Brito ran for 119 yards on eight 
carries and caught three passes for 138 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Western then scored 22 consecutive points to take a 29-9 lead. Chambers 
connected on a five-yard touchdown pass to Justin Starkey with 3:41 left in the 
second quarter. As time ran out in the first half, David Bell kicked a 27-yard 
field goal. In the second half, he later returned an interception 31 yards for 
a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Chambers ran in from six yards out to make the score 22-9. 
</P>
<P>
 Brito capped Cypress' offense with a 72-yard touchdown run with 9:50 left to 
make the score 29-16. 
</P>
<P>
 Chambers had seven completions of 20 yards or more. Lee and Bell caught six of 
those passes for a combined 144 yards. TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</TEXT>
